4. Ultralytics / AGPL-3.0 boundary
----------------------------------

The deployed plugin runtime DOES NOT import the `ultralytics` Python
package. The default inference path is ONNX Runtime or OpenVINO, both
permissively licensed, consuming pre-exported `.onnx` files placed in
`/var/lib/p3-vision-nx/models/`.

To produce those `.onnx` files from an Ultralytics YOLO checkpoint, run
the Ultralytics CLI on your own development machine (NOT on the
mediaserver). Doing so places the AGPL-3.0 obligations of Ultralytics on
that development machine only; the exported weights are model output and
are not considered a derivative work of the Ultralytics Python source.
This mirrors the pattern used by Network Optix's own conversion tutorials
at https://github.com/scailable/nxai-model-to-onnx.

An OPTIONAL adapter that does import ultralytics at runtime is kept in
`python/optional/adapter_pytorch.py`. If you choose to install and use it,
your deployment becomes subject to AGPL-3.0 (network-service copyleft
included). The default install in README.md does NOT install ultralytics
and does NOT include this adapter.

